In each case, the respective N-oxide and the agriculturally acceptable salts of the compounds as further defined below are encompassed. Compounds 1-1 to 1-31 comprise chirai centers and they are generally obtained in the form of racemates. The R- and S-enantiomers of the compounds contained as component I in the compositions according to the invention can be separated and isolated in pure form with methods known by the skilled person, e.g. by using chiral HPLC. Suitable for use in the compositions are both the enantiomers and compositions thereof. Furthermore, said components I can be present in different crystal modifications, which may differ in biological activity.

